Program: Free Thinking
Title: Marilynne Robinson
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b09yh833
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 12 Apr 2018
When President Obama met the American essayist and fiction writer Marilynne Robinson they discussed shared values, citiizenship and Christianity. She talks to Rana Mitter about her definition of Puritanism, the radical history of the mid west states, the use of religion in current American political rhetoric and the biblical cadences of her fiction. Marilynne Robinson is the author of novels including Gilead, Lila, Home and her new collection of Essays is called What Are We Doing Here ? Show less